      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "3fc9f7acfccb094b",
      "text": "According to these »progressive epochs of the economic formation of society« (Marx, Preface 1859 To the Critique of Political Economy), the conceptual mental work also changes. But their common character as formations of commodity production – in contrast to the »common modes of production« described by Marx as predominantly »asiatic«, which precede them altogether – corresponds to a common basic stock of conceptual form of thought, thanks to which even today there exists an intellectual context of discussion reaching back over 2500 years to the beginning of Greek philosophy. "
