        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "3fc9f7acfccb094b",
        "text": "According to these »progressive epochs of the economic formation of society« (Marx, Preface 1859 To the Critique of Political Economy), the conceptual mental work also changes. But their common character as formations of commodity production – in contrast to the »common modes of production« described by Marx as predominantly »asiatic«, which precede them altogether – corresponds to a common basic stock of conceptual form of thought, thanks to which even today there exists an intellectual context of discussion reaching back over 2500 years to the beginning of Greek philosophy. This pure formal commonality in the intellectual field, which encompasses all stages of commodity production and is unchanging in itself, has an equally formal correlate in the economic field, which is emphasized by Marx, among others, in the following way: >>Whatever the sequence of periodic reproductions and previous accumulations that the capital functioning today has gone through, it always preserves its original virginity. As long as the laws of exchange are respected in each act of exchange, the mode of appropriation [of surplus labor] can undergo a total revolution without touching in any way the right of property proper to commodity production. This same right is in force, as it was in the beginning, when the product belonged to the producer, and when the latter, exchanging equivalent for equivalent, could enrich himself only through his own labor, so also in the capitalist period, when the social wealth becomes, to an ever-increasing degree, the property of those who are able to appropriate ever anew the unpaid labor of others. Translated with www.DeepL.com/Translator (free version)"
